comment: Two equivalent ways to express the Power Set Axiom. Note that ~ ax-pow is not used by the proof. When ~ ax-pow is assumed and ` A ` is a set, both sides of the biconditional hold. In ZF, both sides hold if and only if ` A ` is a set (see ~ pwexr ). (Contributed by NM, 22-Jun-2009.)
